Vulnerability 2 – Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

Description

The application reflects user input without sanitization, allowing JavaScript execution.

CVSS Score

6.1 (Medium)

URL

http://demo.testfire.net/search.jsp

HTTP Request

GET /search.jsp?q=<script>alert(1)</script> HTTP/1.1
Host: demo.testfire.net

HTTP Response

<script>alert(1)</script>

OWASP Category

OWASP Top 10 2021 – A03: Injection (XSS)

Payload Used

<script>alert(1)</script>

Steps to Reproduce

1. Open the search page.


2. Intercept the request with Burp Suite.


3. Replace the search parameter with the payload.


4. Forward the request.


5. Observe the JavaScript alert.



Screenshots

Burp request

Burp response

Browser alert box


Impact

Session hijacking

Cookie theft

Malicious script execution


Remediation

Validate and sanitize all user input.

Encode output before displaying it.

Implement a Content Security Policy (CSP).


